tudies, they highlight how the ideology of authoritarian and liberal regimes has affected the practical enactment of forensic expertise. They also emphasise the influence of images of masculinity and femininity on the performance of experts and on their assessment of evidence, victims and perpetrators. This book is an important contribution to our knowledge of modern European forensic practices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aMEDICAL / Forensic Medicine.2bisacsh1 aAdam, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergers, Lara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergers, Lara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDirven, Pauline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDirven, Pauline, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDixon, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaribian, Taline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartínez, Sara Serrano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrlandi, Franco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParfenchyk, Volha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuberg, Willemijn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuberg, Willemijn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSantos, Filipe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSerrano Martínez, Sara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSkålevåg, Svein Atle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular